.o_content(style='margin-left:-15px;margin-right:-15px;')
    .o_view_manager_content
        .o_form_view.o_form_editable
            .o_form_sheet_bg
                .o_form_sheet
                    table.o_group.o_inner_group
                        tbody
                            tr
                                td.o_td_label(colspan='1')
                                    label.o_form_label.o_form_label_help(for='o_field_input_170', data-original-title='', title='')
                                        | Nomenclature Name
                                td(colspan='1', style='width: 50%;')
                                    input#o_field_input_170.o_form_input.o_form_field.o_form_required(maxlength='32', type='text')
                                td.o_td_label(colspan='1')
                                    label.o_form_label.o_form_label_help(for='o_field_input_171', data-original-title='', title='')
                                        | UPC/EAN Conversion
                                td(colspan='1', style='width: 50%;')
                                    select#o_field_input_171.o_form_input.o_form_field.o_form_required(name='upc_ean_conv')
                                        option(value='false')
                                        option(value='"none"') Never
                                        option(value='"ean2upc"') EAN-13 to UPC-A
                                        option(value='"upc2ean"') UPC-A to EAN-13
                                        option(value='"always"') Always
                    div
                        p
                            i Barcodes Nomenclatures
                            |  define how barcodes are recognized and categorized.
                            |                                 When a barcode is scanned it is associated to the
                            i first
                            |  rule with a matching
                            |                                 pattern. The pattern syntax is that of regular expression, and a barcode is matched
                            |                                 if the regular expression matches a prefix of the barcode.
                        p
                            | Patterns can also define how numerical values, such as weight or price, can be
                            | encoded into the barcode. They are indicated by
                            code {NNN}
                            |  where the N's
                            |                                 define where the number's digits are encoded. Floats are also supported with the
                            |                                 decimals indicated with D's, such as
                            code {NNNDD}
                            | . In these cases,
                            |                                 the barcode field on the associated records
                            i must
                            |  show these digits as
                            |                                 zeroes.
                    Tabledrag(v-bind:tableheader='tableheader', v-bind:tabledata="tabledata", v-bind:tablefoot="tablefoot")